What you need to know:

In their statement, Fifa said that Ahmad had "breached his duty of loyalty, offered gifts and other benefits, mismanaged funds and abused his position as the Caf President".Ahmad has also been fined 200,000 Swiss francs ($220,000) by Fifa for the misdeeds, which related to "the organisation and financing of an Umrah pilgrimage to Mecca" and his involvement in Caf's dealings with a sports equipment company.